import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the correlation between u and v?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.ylabel('Frequency')

    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist2d(data['u'], data['v'], bins=30, cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    plt.colorbar(label='Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the joint distribution of u and v?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3)
    kmeans.fit(data)
    labels = kmeans.predict(data)
    
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'], c=labels, cmap='viridis')
    
    plt.title("Are there any clusters or groups in the data?")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
